<h1 class="h2 mb-3">Terms of Service &amp; Community Guidelines</h1>
<p>By creating an account, you agree to use TideTogether responsibly and in accordance with the guidelines below. These terms exist to keep the platform safe and productive for all Northwestern students.</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">Community Guidelines</h2>
<ul class="mt-2">
  <li><strong>Be respectful.</strong> Treat every member of the community with courtesy and professionalism.</li>
  <li><strong>No harassment.</strong> Bullying, threats, hate speech, or targeted harassment of any kind is strictly prohibited.</li>
  <li><strong>No inappropriate or profane content.</strong> Keep all messages, group names, and shared content appropriate for an academic setting.</li>
  <li><strong>No spam.</strong> Do not send unsolicited or repetitive messages, or use the platform for advertising.</li>
  <li><strong>School-appropriate content only.</strong> All content must be suitable for a university academic environment and comply with Northwestern's student conduct policies.</li>
  <li><strong>Misuse may result in removal.</strong> Accounts found to be in violation of these guidelines may be suspended or permanently removed without notice.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">Your Account</h2>
<p>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account and for all activity that occurs under it. Do not share your credentials with others.</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">Changes to These Terms</h2>
<p>We may update these terms as the platform evolves. Continued use of TideTogether after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.</p>

<p class="mt-3 mb-0">If you have questions or concerns, contact the project maintainers via the repository linked in the site footer.</p>
